---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NewsletterSignup from '../components/NewsletterSignup.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Why we started A Green Family — and what we believe about sustainable living for real families."
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-14">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-10 text-center">
      <p class="text-6xl mb-4">🌿</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl text-forest mb-3">About A Green Family</h1>
      <p class="text-ink-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
        We believe every family can make a difference — and that it doesn't have to be hard, expensive, or all-or-nothing.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Story section -->
    <div class="prose prose-green prose-lg max-w-none">

      <h2>Why I started this</h2>
      <p>
        Like most parents, I wanted to leave the world in a better state than I found it. But every time I looked into "going green," the advice seemed designed for people with unlimited time, money, and patience — not for families juggling school pickups, grocery runs, and soccer practice.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm Leandro, and I started A Green Family because I needed a resource that met families where they actually are. Not a lifestyle magazine for the already-converted. A practical guide for people like me who care but also have real lives.
      </p>

      <h2>What this site is about</h2>
      <p>
        Every article here is about one thing: <strong>making a specific green change easier.</strong> That means:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Honest product recommendations that actually work (including affiliate links — <a href="/disclosure">disclosed here</a>)</li>
        <li>Step-by-step guides written for busy parents, not environmental scientists</li>
        <li>A focus on habits that save money, not just the planet</li>
        <li>Ideas for involving kids, because they're the ones who'll inherit the results</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Progress over perfection. A family that swaps plastic bags for reusable ones and composts their fruit scraps is doing more than one that plans a complete zero-waste lifestyle overhaul for "someday."
      </p>
      <p>
        Small, consistent habits compound. That's what this site is about.
      </p>

      <h2>A note on affiliate links</h2>
      <p>
        Some articles contain links to products on Amazon and Walmart. If you buy through those links, we earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. We only recommend products we believe in and that fit the article's topic — no fake reviews, no pay-to-play. You can read the full <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure here</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have a green tip to share? A product you love? A topic you want covered? Email me at <a href="mailto:hello@agreenfamily.com">hello@agreenfamily.com</a> — I read everything.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- Newsletter -->
    <NewsletterSignup />

  </article>
</Layout>
